Description: Fragment of handle at neck join of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with owl on fulmen symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 188a, 11. Name Eutaktos. From same die as BM 2011,5004.86 and Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0611.31.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0972)
